 oliver wyman  company and merged these with some of the consultancy businesses from previous acquisitions particularly the mercer business under the brand name of oliver wyman on july   marsh completed the acquisition of kroll inc jeffrey w greenberg called it an important strategic step the company had employed terrorism expert john oneill formerly of the federal bureau of investigation on october   new york state attorney general eliot spitzer announced the initiation of a civil action against marsh alleging impropriety in the steering of clients to insurers with whom the company maintained payoff agreements and for soliciting rigged bids for insurance contracts from the insurers the attorney general announced that two aig executives pleaded guilty to criminal charges in connection with this illegal course of conduct and stated there is simply no responsible argument for a system that rigs bids stifles competition and cheats customers ceo jeffrey w greenberg resigned several weeks later the suit was ultimately settled out of court on january   marsh  mclennan agreed on an million settlement for its bidrigging practices in july  marsh  mclennan cos inc was ranked first in business insurances worlds largest brokers list in august  marsh completed the sale of its putnam investments division to greatwest lifeco inc a financial services holding company controlled by canadabased power financial corp after it settled charges of market timing on september   brian m storms the ceo of marshs insurance brokerage unit resigned as michael g cherkasky explained his departure we now need a different set of leadership and operational skills september  attacksedit at the time of the september  attacks in the united states in  the corporation held offices on eight floors of the north tower of the world trade center from  to  when american airlines flight  crashed into the building their offices spanned the entire impact zone from floors  to  everybody present in the offices at the time of the attack died as all stairwells at impact zone were destroyedblocked by the plane crash and the firm lost  employees and  contractors cantor fitzgerald is the only company to have lost more in the attack operating segments and subsidiariesedit marsh  mclennan companies is composed of two primary business segments risk and insurance services and consulting risk and insurance servicesedit marsh which provides insurance broking and risk management consulting peter zaffino has been the president and ceo since  guy carpenter a risk and reinsurance intermediary consultingedit mercer offering health retirement talent and investment consulting services oliver wyman group a collection of management consulting firms including oliver wyman formerly mercer management consulting mercer oliver wyman and oliver wyman delta as well as lippincott and nera economic consulting managementedit president ceo dan glaser since jan   chairman h edward hanway nonexecutive chairman –present see alsoedit willis towers watson referencesedit  a b milestones of marsh  mclennan companies retrieved    a b c d e f marsh  mclennan  annual report form k filing date feb   secdatabasecom retrieved may     mmc profile  marsh  mclennan companies inc yahoo finance yahoo retrieved  may    bloomberg businessweeks ranking of topperforming companies bloomberg businessweek january     world rankings retrieved    milestones of marsh  mclennan companies mmc retrieved  december    chronological list of events for marsh and mclennan   scott  scott llcs clients seek leadership roles in benefits lawsuit against marsh  mclennan plan participants including current and former employees seek remedies at law under erisa february   retrieved jul     business insurance leading brokers  marsh  mclennan cos inc business insurance retrieved  aug    marsh completes sale of putnam investments to greatwest lifeco insurancejournalcom august     roberts sally september   storms out as marsh chief business insurance   spe